(Internal responsibilities ‚Äî the core duties of a national system)
These are the non negotiable, high level responsibilities that a central government must handle because they cannot be effectively managed at local or regional levels.
1. Public Service and Administrative Excellence
‚Ä¢	Deliver essential national services efficiently and transparently.
‚Ä¢	Operate as a professional administrative body, not a political class.
‚Ä¢	Maintain infrastructure, justice systems, and national logistics with competence and neutrality.
2. Enabling Local Self Governance
‚Ä¢	Push decision making downward to communities.
‚Ä¢	Allow local norms, customs, and conflict resolution systems to flourish.
‚Ä¢	Intervene only when issues exceed local capacity or violate core rights.
3. Preserving Cultural Identity and Local Freedom
‚Ä¢	Protect the right of each community to maintain its traditions, values, and way of life.
‚Ä¢	Avoid imposing one cultural standard on all communities.
‚Ä¢	Ensure national law focuses on clear harms, not cultural micromanagement.
4. Maintaining National Stability and Security
‚Ä¢	Defence, borders, currency, and large scale infrastructure.
‚Ä¢	Provide a stable framework within which local communities can thrive.
‚Ä¢	Ensure continuity, safety, and long term planning.
5. High Bandwidth Citizen Input
