‚Ä¢	Independent oversight bodies
Not political, not appointed by parties ‚Äî selected for competence and integrity.
‚Ä¢	Real time monitoring systems
Algorithms and auditors that detect:
o	corruption
o	misuse of funds
o	administrative failure
o	delays or cost overruns
‚Ä¢	Immediate intervention powers
Oversight bodies can:
o	suspend a failing administrator
o	freeze a corrupt project
o	trigger a public review
o	escalate issues to higher layers
‚Ä¢	Citizen triggered reviews
If enough citizens flag a problem, an automatic investigation begins.
This creates a self correcting governance system, similar to how well designed engineering systems detect and isolate faults before they cascade.
‚≠ê In one sentence
High bandwidth citizen input now means full transparency, continuous public participation, and a rapid response oversight system that detects and corrects failures before they become systemic.
üåê Secondary / External Priorities
